==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flitter
<hw>Flit"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To flutter; to move quickly;
<as>as, to <ex>flitter</ex> the cards</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flitter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Flitter
<hw>Flit"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G. <ets>flitter</ets>
spangle, tinsel, <ets>flittern</ets> to make a tremulous motion, to
glitter. Cf. <er>Flitter</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>A rag; a
tatter; a small piece or fragment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flittermouse</ent>⟦br⟧
